info.name: W3C Webdriver API Collection
info.description:
![image](https://opengraph.githubassets.com/fd7f372c18ee57ce39abc33be6a103cdf4c90ae19fbc59c837553d19aee426b9/w3c/webdriver)

This is a collection of all webdriver w3c api end points. 

Thanks to **@christian-bromann** from webdriverIO for the swagger page from which this collection was created.

![logo](https://img.stackshare.io/service/4185/webdriver.io.png)

https://app.swaggerhub.com/apis-docs/christian-bromann/webdriver/2.0.0

you can use this collection to learn and play around with the w3c api endpoints

WebDriver is a remote control interface that enables introspection and control of user agents. It provides a platform- and language-neutral wire protocol as a way for out-of-process programs to remotely instruct the behavior of web browsers.

Contact Support:

 Name: Browser Testing and Tools Working Group
 
Email: public-browser-tools-testing@w3.org
